Read in data

dat <- read.csv("correlation_1.csv")
head(dat)
##   Temperature_20190304 USYD_Veg_strata USYD_Veg_strata_1
## 1                 33.4               4             5-10m
## 2                 25.0               5            10-20m
## 3                 28.0               3              3-5m
## 4                 27.1               4             5-10m
## 5                 26.5               5            10-20m
## 6                 27.2               5            10-20m

Run model

mod <- aov(Temperature_20190304~USYD_Veg_strata_1, data = dat)

Residual analysis

Note that the residuals are very kurtotic and slightly skewed but a transformation does not help much. Its probably okay but need to be somewhat weary of interpretation of results.

par(mfrow = c(2,2))
plot(mod)

par(mfrow = c(1,1))
hist(resid(mod))

Partial F-test

Veg strata is highly significant

anova(mod)

Pairwise comparison using emmeans

The following also is a Tukeys HSD post hoc test and with a pairwise comparison and plot

require(emmeans)
## Loading required package: emmeans
emm_mod <- emmeans(mod, ~USYD_Veg_strata_1)
plot(emm_mod, comparisons = T)
## Warning: Comparison discrepancy in group "1", (1.5-2m) - (3-5m):
##     Target overlap = -0.0087, overlap on graph = 0.0037

pairs(emm_mod)
